tiated and how feelings of alienation limit human identification in any society.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 24. Mai 2022) 0aImmigrantsxBiographyxUnited StatesxUnited States. 0aImmigrantszUnited StatesvBiography. 0aJapanese AmericansvBiography. 0aJapanese AmericansxBiography. 7aLITERARY CRITICISM / General.2bisacsh1 aCreef, Elena Tajima, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aRobinson, Greg, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertRutgers University Press Backlist eBook-Package 2000-2013z978311068861040uhttps://doi.org/10.36019/978081354477940uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780813544779423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780813544779/original  a978-3-11-068861-0  Rutgers University Press Backlist eBook-Package 2000-2013c2000d2013  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_CL_LT  aEBA_EBACKALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_ECL_LT  aEBA_EEBKALL  aEBA_ESSHALL  aEBA_PPALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aPDA11SSHE  aPDA13ENGE  aPDA17SSHEE  aPDA5EBK